Last Updated: 19 March 2026

This SDK License Agreement (the "EULA") applies to, and governs, any access to and use of the software development kit (SDK) being downloaded or used (the "SDK"), and YOU, THE CUSTOMER ACCESSING OR USING THE SDK OR OTHERWISE AGREEING TO THIS EULA (the "Licensee"), ARE AGREEING TO THIS AGREEMENT BY: 

	•	SIGNING THE SDK ORDERING DOCUMENT TO WHICH THIS EULA IS ATTACHED (OR OTHERWISE INCORPORATED BY REFERENCE), IF APPLICABLE (THE "SDK ORDER FORM"); OR 
	•	BY CLICKING ON THE "I ACCEPT" (OR SIMILAR) BUTTON, BY CHECKING A CHECKBOX FOR THE ACCEPTANCE OF THIS AGREEMENT, OR OTHERWISE BY DOWNLOADING, ACCESSING OR USING THE SDK, 

WHICHEVER IS EARLIER (SUCH DATE, THE "Effective Date").

This EULA forms an integral part of the agreement entered into between Licensee and Pixellot Ltd. (or, if applicable, the other Pixellot entity) ("Pixellot") pursuant to which Licensee has purchased its subscription to Pixellot's OTT video capture streaming service (such agreement, the "OTT Subscription Agreement"). 

To the extent of any conflict or inconsistency between this EULA and the SDK Order Form, the latter shall prevail. 

An individual entering into this EULA on behalf of the Licensee, represents that he/she has the right, authority and capacity to act on behalf of the Licensee and to bind the Licensee to this EULA. If an individual is using an organization's email address, such organization shall be deemed the Licensee.

Unless the context clearly requires otherwise, references herein to the "SDK" shall also be deemed to include any related APIs and documentation that are made available to Licensee with the SDK.

